The paper deals with activity recognition from videos, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves graph matching, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of GPUs for parallel processing suggests a focus on optimization and efficiency, which is often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
